  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_b420c8ee27be5d55d68876b48f6254a1">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>Variety of published materials, mostly in languages of Nepal. Many serials, pamphlets, ephemera.  Also, a photo album (ca. 1990) made by a Cornell student, presumably one in the Cornell Nepal Study Abroad Program, or perhaps on another trip that took students to Nepal.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite audience="internal" id="aspace_6674b45c058151ba9c32c797466ed999">
    <head>Preferred Citation</head>
<p>March and Holmberg collection on Nepal's ethnicities and the People's War, #8674. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
  <bioghist audience="internal" id="aspace_a4aa0ce301eee96c3fa29099af927b27">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Cornell anthropologists Kathryn March and David Holmberg worked in the Himalayas for several decades. They collected intensively on Nepali politics and cultures during the period of the People's War, 1996-2002, and its aftermath.</p>  </bioghist>
